1
00:00:01,763 --> 00:00:04,963
-ONCE UPON A TIME,
THERE WAS A KNIGHT.
THE KNIGHT NEVER FALTERED
IN HIS DUTY,

2
00:00:04,963 --> 00:00:06,796
NO MATTER WHAT IT WAS.

3
00:00:06,796 --> 00:00:10,096
HE DIDN'T EVEN FALTER
WHEN DUTY DEMANDED

4
00:00:10,096 --> 00:00:12,463
HE TAKE THE LIFE OF HIS LOVER.

5
00:00:12,463 --> 00:00:15,863
HIS DEDICATION
WAS WHAT HE TOOK PRIDE IN.

6
00:00:15,863 --> 00:00:18,796
BUT THE KNIGHT
COULDN'T DO ANYTHING

7
00:00:18,796 --> 00:00:22,429
BUT CARRY OUT HIS DUTY,
AND EVEN AFTER DEATH,

8
00:00:22,429 --> 00:00:25,863
HE STILL SEEKS A DUTY
TO CARRY OUT.

9
00:00:25,863 --> 00:00:28,863
THEY SAY THE KNIGHT
WHO BECAME A GHOST

10
00:00:28,863 --> 00:00:32,663
AND NOW HAUNTS THIS WORLD
HOLDS IN HIS HAND

11
00:00:32,663 --> 00:00:37,429
THE BLOOD-STAINED SWORD
THAT PIERCED HIS LOVER'S BREAST.

12
00:00:37,429 --> 00:00:39,963
[ RITSUKO OKAZAKI'S
"MORNING GRACE" PLAYS ]

13
00:00:52,429 --> 00:00:54,896
-[ SINGING IN JAPANESE ]

14
00:01:20,363 --> 00:01:23,529
[ SINGING CONTINUES ]

15
00:02:05,596 --> 00:02:08,496
[ TCHAIKOVSKY'S
"FINAL WALTZ AND APOTHEOSIS"
FROM "THE NUTCRACKER" PLAYS ]

16
00:02:32,158 --> 00:02:33,958
[ HORSE NEIGHS ]

17
00:02:36,725 --> 00:02:38,925
[ HORSE NEIGHS ]

18
00:02:41,125 --> 00:02:41,958
-[ GRUNTS ]

19
00:02:41,958 --> 00:02:43,858
[ SWORDS CLANGING ]

20
00:02:44,558 --> 00:02:45,658
[ HORSE NEIGHS ]

21
00:02:45,658 --> 00:02:48,125
[ SWORDS CLANGING ]

22
00:02:48,858 --> 00:02:49,925
AAH!

23
00:02:54,025 --> 00:02:55,058
[ GASPS ]

24
00:03:00,025 --> 00:03:01,458
WHAT WAS THAT?

25
00:03:10,491 --> 00:03:15,129
[ SCREAMING ]

26
00:03:15,129 --> 00:03:16,429
-THEY SAY
THAT HE'S APPEARED AGAIN.

27
00:03:16,429 --> 00:03:18,595
-THE INFAMOUS AND CURSED
GHOST KNIGHT.

28
00:03:18,595 --> 00:03:19,495
-HUH?
-HUH?

29
00:03:19,495 --> 00:03:20,929
-HEY, DUCK.
-HEY, DUCK.

30
00:03:20,929 --> 00:03:22,962
-WHAT'S WRONG?
YOU'RE ALL SPACED OUT.

31
00:03:22,962 --> 00:03:25,062
-OH, NO, NOTHING'S WRONG.

32
00:03:25,062 --> 00:03:27,729
-OH, COME TO THINK OF IT,
TODAY IS...

33
00:03:27,729 --> 00:03:28,929
-OH!

34
00:03:28,929 --> 00:03:31,695
-Both: THE DAY FAKIR COMES BACK
FROM SUSPENSION!

35
00:03:31,695 --> 00:03:32,729
-HUH?

36
00:03:32,729 --> 00:03:34,595
-I WONDER
JUST HOW WRETCHED HE'LL LOOK

37
00:03:34,595 --> 00:03:35,729
WHEN HE COMES IN TODAY.

38
00:03:35,729 --> 00:03:37,395
-SO HE'S BACK TODAY.
-HUH?

39
00:03:37,395 --> 00:03:39,829
ARE YOU COMPLETELY
A FAKIR GIRL, TOO, NOW?

40
00:03:39,829 --> 00:03:41,195
-WHAT? NO.

41
00:03:41,195 --> 00:03:43,795
NO, I'M TELLING YOU, FAKIR AND I
AREN'T ANYTHING LIKE THAT.

42
00:03:43,795 --> 00:03:45,229
WE'RE NOT ANYTHING.

43
00:03:45,229 --> 00:03:47,162
-BUT, HEY, IF YOU'RE REALLY THAT
SERIOUS ABOUT THE WHOLE THING,

44
00:03:47,162 --> 00:03:48,995
YOU'RE MY FRIEND,
AND I GOT TO SUPPORT YOU,

45
00:03:48,995 --> 00:03:50,095
DON'T I?
-AND ME, TOO.

46
00:03:50,095 --> 00:03:51,895
I'LL SUPPORT YOU
WITH EVERYTHING I'VE GOT.

47
00:03:51,895 --> 00:03:53,062
-NO, SEE --

48
00:03:53,062 --> 00:03:54,562
-Both:
FIRST UP, THE LOVE CONFESSION!

49
00:03:54,562 --> 00:03:55,429
-OH!

50
00:03:57,929 --> 00:03:58,962
-WHAT'S THIS?

51
00:03:58,962 --> 00:04:00,629
-THEY SEEM A BIT FREAKY.

52
00:04:00,629 --> 00:04:03,662
-JUST WALK PAST 'EM.
DON'T MAKE EYE CONTACT.

53
00:04:03,662 --> 00:04:05,495
-YOU BE CAREFUL, TOO, DUCK.

54
00:04:05,495 --> 00:04:06,462
-A DUCK!

55
00:04:08,295 --> 00:04:09,729
-YOU'RE A DUCK!

56
00:04:09,729 --> 00:04:10,795
-[ GASPS ]

57
00:04:10,795 --> 00:04:12,995
-I, MYSELF, AM A SHRIMP,
BY THE WAY.

58
00:04:12,995 --> 00:04:16,195
WE ARE HERE EXPRESSING
OUR OWN INTANGIBLE INNER WORLDS

59
00:04:16,195 --> 00:04:18,529
IN A MORE EXTERNAL
AND CONCRETE FORM,

60
00:04:18,529 --> 00:04:20,362
AND I CAN SEE YOUR IMAGE
IS THAT OF A DUCK.

61
00:04:20,362 --> 00:04:21,795
-RIGHT.

62
00:04:21,795 --> 00:04:24,795
-SO, TELL ME, WHICH DIVISION
ARE YOU PART OF AS A STUDENT?

63
00:04:24,795 --> 00:04:26,862
-I'M IN THE BALLET DIVISION.
-REALLY?

64
00:04:26,862 --> 00:04:29,062
-YOU THINK SHE --
-WHY DON'T WE ASK HER?

65
00:04:29,062 --> 00:04:31,462
-EXCUSE US.
DO YOU KNOW THE WONDERFUL MYTHO?

66
00:04:31,462 --> 00:04:32,862
-UH, YES.
[ ALL GASP ]

67
00:04:32,862 --> 00:04:35,195
-WELL, YOU SEE,
THE TRUTH OF THE MATTER IS,

68
00:04:35,195 --> 00:04:38,029
WE'VE BEEN TRYING TO FIND A BOY
TO DANCE BALLET FOR US

69
00:04:38,029 --> 00:04:39,662
IN OUR UPCOMING SHOW.
-UH...

70
00:04:39,662 --> 00:04:41,062
[ BOTH SIGH ]

71
00:04:41,062 --> 00:04:43,629
-WE'D REALLY LOVE TO ASK THE
WONDERFUL MYTHO TO DO IT, BUT...

72
00:04:43,629 --> 00:04:45,129
-ASK MYTHO?

73
00:04:45,129 --> 00:04:48,429
-AS PROOF, THEN, YOU'LL GIVE ME
YOUR BEAUTIFUL HEART.

74
00:04:48,429 --> 00:04:51,362
<i>-NO.</i>
<i>MYTHO, AS HE IS NOW...</i>

75
00:04:51,362 --> 00:04:52,429
[ GASPS ]

76
00:04:52,429 --> 00:04:55,195
UM, WOULD IT BE OKAY
IF FAKIR DID IT?

77
00:04:55,195 --> 00:04:56,029
[ ALL GASP ]

78
00:04:56,029 --> 00:04:57,229
-HE'S SO SCARY.

79
00:04:57,229 --> 00:04:59,695
-HE'S THE GUY THAT PUSHES
PEOPLE HE DOESN'T LIKE

80
00:04:59,695 --> 00:05:00,962
OUT THE WINDOW, RIGHT?

81
00:05:00,962 --> 00:05:02,462
-NO, THAT'S A BIG FAT LIE,

82
00:05:02,462 --> 00:05:05,262
AND HE'S JUST AS GOOD AT BALLET
AS MYTHO IS, SO --

83
00:05:05,262 --> 00:05:08,429
-THAT'S TRUE. AS THINGS STAND,
WE COULD USE SENIOR FAKIR.

84
00:05:08,429 --> 00:05:09,629
-WHAT? REALLY?

85
00:05:09,629 --> 00:05:11,962
-HERE YOU GO.
THIS IS A COPY OF THE SCRIPT.

86
00:05:11,962 --> 00:05:14,362
COULD YOU GIVE IT
TO SENIOR FAKIR FOR US

87
00:05:14,362 --> 00:05:16,262
WHEN YOU SEE HIM?
-OF COURSE.

88
00:05:16,262 --> 00:05:17,962
THANK YOU.

89
00:05:23,395 --> 00:05:25,029
-HI.

90
00:05:25,029 --> 00:05:28,029
I'M SO GLAD YOU'VE COME BACK
TO SCHOOL, FAKIR.

91
00:05:28,029 --> 00:05:30,962
I'VE BEEN WAITING FOR YOU.

92
00:05:30,962 --> 00:05:31,895
[ CHUCKLES ]

93
00:05:31,895 --> 00:05:33,895
[ ALL MURMURING ]

94
00:05:33,895 --> 00:05:36,495
-[ SWOONS ]

95
00:05:36,495 --> 00:05:38,629
-WHY DID YOU COME BACK?

96
00:05:38,629 --> 00:05:42,362
-I AM HERE TO PROTECT MYTHO.
THAT'S ALL.

97
00:05:42,362 --> 00:05:44,495
-[ CHUCKLES ]
PROTECT? HOW?

98
00:05:44,495 --> 00:05:48,495
YOU'RE A KNIGHT WHO COULDN'T
EVEN FIND THE STRENGTH TO DIE.

99
00:05:48,495 --> 00:05:49,962
WHAT CAN YOU DO?

100
00:05:49,962 --> 00:05:53,895
THE KNIGHT'S ROLE IN THE STORY
WAS TO BE TORN IN TWO AND DIE,

101
00:05:53,895 --> 00:05:57,495
BUT NOT ONLY WERE YOU SAVED
IN THAT UNSEEMLY WAY --

102
00:05:57,495 --> 00:06:00,262
YOU'VE GOT THE NERVE
TO STILL BE ALIVE.

103
00:06:00,262 --> 00:06:03,795
THE STORY NO LONGER
HAS NEED OF YOU.

104
00:06:03,795 --> 00:06:07,895
NOW YOU'LL JUST FADE AWAY
AND BE FORGOTTEN.

105
00:06:07,895 --> 00:06:11,929
WELCOME BACK, FAKIR.
IT'S GOOD TO SEE YOU.

106
00:06:11,929 --> 00:06:13,929
-WONDER WHAT KIND OF PLAY IT IS.

107
00:06:13,929 --> 00:06:16,962
OH, FAKIR.

108
00:06:16,962 --> 00:06:18,562
GOOD MORNING, FAKIR.

109
00:06:18,562 --> 00:06:19,729
-THIS IS EARLY FOR YOU.

110
00:06:19,729 --> 00:06:21,229
-HEY, DO YOU LIKE PLAYS, FAKIR?

111
00:06:21,229 --> 00:06:22,429
BALLET IS DANCING,

112
00:06:22,429 --> 00:06:24,695
BUT THERE'S STORIES TO IT
AND STUFF, TOO, YOU KNOW,

113
00:06:24,695 --> 00:06:26,562
SO IT'S KIND OF SORT OF
LIKE A PLAY.

114
00:06:26,562 --> 00:06:27,895
I MEAN --
-SPIT IT OUT.

115
00:06:27,895 --> 00:06:30,229
-WELL, YOU SEE,
THE PEOPLE FROM THE DRAMA CLUB

116
00:06:30,229 --> 00:06:32,195
SAY THEY WANT YOU
TO DANCE THE BALLET

117
00:06:32,195 --> 00:06:34,562
IN THIS PLAY THEY'RE GONNA BE
PUTTING ON SOON,

118
00:06:34,562 --> 00:06:35,629
SO READ THIS SCRIPT.

119
00:06:35,629 --> 00:06:37,529
OKAY?
-[ GASPS ]

120
00:06:37,529 --> 00:06:39,462
-'CAUSE IF YOU ENTER
THE CLUBS AND STUFF,

121
00:06:39,462 --> 00:06:41,995
YOU'VE GOT ALL THE MORE REASON
TO COME TO SCHOOL, RIGHT?

122
00:06:41,995 --> 00:06:44,629
RIGHT NOW, I WANT YOU TO STICK
TO MYTHO AS CLOSE AS YOU CAN

123
00:06:44,629 --> 00:06:47,129
SO THAT WAY --

124
00:06:47,129 --> 00:06:48,129
UM, FAKIR?

125
00:06:48,129 --> 00:06:50,562
-I DON'T NEED YOU TO DIRECT ME.

126
00:06:50,562 --> 00:06:53,429
-OKAY.
I'LL LEAVE IT TO YOU, THEN.

127
00:06:53,429 --> 00:06:54,895
-HEY, WAIT!

128
00:06:58,562 --> 00:06:59,962
[ PIANO MUSIC PLAYS ]

129
00:06:59,962 --> 00:07:01,029
-MR. FAKIR.

130
00:07:01,029 --> 00:07:02,229
-MR. CAT?

131
00:07:02,229 --> 00:07:05,662
-BAD BLOOD BETWEEN PEOPLE
EVENTUALLY GOES AWAY,

132
00:07:05,662 --> 00:07:08,595
EVEN WHEN YOU'RE NOT CONSUMED
BY WORRY.

133
00:07:08,595 --> 00:07:11,229
OH, ARE YOU DOING
A CLUB ACTIVITY?

134
00:07:11,229 --> 00:07:12,562
THAT'S EXCELLENT.

135
00:07:12,562 --> 00:07:15,995
BOYS AND GIRLS SWEATING
YOUTHFUL SWEAT TOGETHER

136
00:07:15,995 --> 00:07:18,062
ARE WORKING TOWARDS ONE GOAL,

137
00:07:18,062 --> 00:07:20,695
AND FROM THAT
COMES A NEW MEANING,

138
00:07:20,695 --> 00:07:23,762
AND EVENTUALLY LOVE BLOOMS,
AND MARRIAGE,

139
00:07:23,762 --> 00:07:25,729
AND -- OH.

140
00:07:25,729 --> 00:07:28,762
ANYWAY, IT'S IMPORTANT
TO HAVE THE DESIRE

141
00:07:28,762 --> 00:07:31,729
FOR A POSITIVE INVOLVEMENT
IN SOMETHING.

142
00:07:31,729 --> 00:07:32,929
-MR. CAT, WAIT.

143
00:07:32,929 --> 00:07:34,129
-YES, FAKIR?

144
00:07:34,129 --> 00:07:36,162
-DO YOU THINK IT'S POSSIBLE
TO TURN

145
00:07:36,162 --> 00:07:38,729
A LOVE THAT'S BEEN MADE IMPURE
BACK TO NORMAL?

146
00:07:38,729 --> 00:07:41,495
-YOU RAISE
A RATHER THORNY ISSUE.

147
00:07:41,495 --> 00:07:44,629
WHAT IS IT THAT DEFINES
AN IMPURE LOVE?

148
00:07:44,629 --> 00:07:48,995
AFTER ALL, WHO CAN SAY
THAT ODILE'S LOVE IS IMPURE?

149
00:07:48,995 --> 00:07:50,695
-WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

150
00:07:56,829 --> 00:07:58,462
THIS IS --

151
00:07:58,462 --> 00:08:01,462
-WONDER IF FAKIR
READ THE SCRIPT.

152
00:08:01,462 --> 00:08:03,795
OH, IS THIS THE PLACE?

153
00:08:03,795 --> 00:08:05,629
HELLO, IN THERE?

154
00:08:05,629 --> 00:08:08,729
IS THERE ANYBODY IN HERE?

155
00:08:08,729 --> 00:08:12,429
MAYBE FAKIR IS...NOT HERE.

156
00:08:12,429 --> 00:08:13,295
-HEY.

157
00:08:13,295 --> 00:08:14,229
-WHAT?!

158
00:08:16,429 --> 00:08:17,795
FAKIR, YOU CAME AFTER ALL.

159
00:08:17,795 --> 00:08:19,129
-WOULD YOU MIND TELLING ME

160
00:08:19,129 --> 00:08:20,962
WHERE THE REST
OF THIS SCRIPT IS?

161
00:08:20,962 --> 00:08:22,495
-WHAT DO YOU MEAN, "THE REST"?

162
00:08:22,495 --> 00:08:24,695
-THE SCRIPT CUTS OFF
RIGHT IN THE MIDDLE.

163
00:08:24,695 --> 00:08:25,962
-IT CUTS OFF?
-WHAT?

164
00:08:25,962 --> 00:08:26,995
-UH...

165
00:08:26,995 --> 00:08:28,395
-SO WHAT YOU'RE SAYING IS,

166
00:08:28,395 --> 00:08:30,895
YOU DUMPED A SCRIPT
YOU HADN'T EVEN READ ON ME?

167
00:08:30,895 --> 00:08:33,029
-[ CHUCKLES ]
BUT EVERYBODY KEPT SAYING

168
00:08:33,029 --> 00:08:35,695
HOW THE PART WAS TOTALLY PERFECT
FOR YOU AND STUFF.

169
00:08:35,695 --> 00:08:38,295
-[ SIGHS ] A GHOST KNIGHT
IS PERFECT FOR ME, HUH?

170
00:08:38,295 --> 00:08:40,329
-IT'S ABOUT A GHOST KNIGHT?

171
00:08:40,329 --> 00:08:42,262
WHAT KIND OF STORY IS IT?

172
00:08:43,862 --> 00:08:46,962
-HE WAS HAILED
AS THE STRONGEST OF KNIGHTS.

173
00:08:46,962 --> 00:08:48,662
ENEMY NATIONS FEARED HIM.

174
00:08:48,662 --> 00:08:51,962
THE KNIGHT BELIEVED
HIS DUTY WAS TO RISK HIS LIFE

175
00:08:51,962 --> 00:08:53,395
TO PROTECT HIS KING.

176
00:08:53,395 --> 00:08:55,262
HE EVEN KILLED HIS OWN LOVER,

177
00:08:55,262 --> 00:08:57,629
WHO WAS A SPY
FOR AN ENEMY KINGDOM,

178
00:08:57,629 --> 00:08:58,895
WITHOUT FALTERING.

179
00:08:58,895 --> 00:09:01,795
EVENTUALLY,
THE TWO NATIONS MADE PEACE,

180
00:09:01,795 --> 00:09:04,395
BUT THE KNIGHT WAS CAST
INTO EXILE

181
00:09:04,395 --> 00:09:07,295
AND THENCEFORTH KNEW
NEITHER WHOM TO PROTECT

182
00:09:07,295 --> 00:09:08,595
NOR WHOM TO DEFEAT.

183
00:09:08,595 --> 00:09:09,795
HE DIED THAT WAY,

184
00:09:09,795 --> 00:09:12,329
HIS SOUL CURSED TO WANDER
THIS WORLD.

185
00:09:12,329 --> 00:09:15,162
IT'S AT THIS POINT
WHERE THE SCRIPT CUTS OFF.

186
00:09:15,162 --> 00:09:17,929
-THAT'S KIND OF A SAD STORY,
DON'T YOU THINK?

187
00:09:17,929 --> 00:09:18,762
[ GASPS ]

188
00:09:18,762 --> 00:09:20,862
-OH, NO, I THINK IT'S A RIOT.

189
00:09:20,862 --> 00:09:21,995
-RUE!

190
00:09:21,995 --> 00:09:24,762
-A WANDERING KNIGHT
UNABLE TO DO ANYTHING --

191
00:09:24,762 --> 00:09:28,129
I THINK THE ROLE FITS YOU
TO A "T," FAKIR.

192
00:09:28,129 --> 00:09:29,262
[ CHUCKLES ]

193
00:09:29,262 --> 00:09:30,462
-RUE, WAIT!

194
00:09:30,462 --> 00:09:32,595
WHERE'D SHE GO?

195
00:09:32,595 --> 00:09:35,229
-OH, IT'S MISS DUCK.

196
00:09:35,229 --> 00:09:37,462
-UM, FAKIR IS --

197
00:09:37,462 --> 00:09:40,429
-WOW.
YOU REALLY BROUGHT HIM ALONG?

198
00:09:42,129 --> 00:09:43,729
-THIS IS THE ORIGINAL.

199
00:09:43,729 --> 00:09:47,029
TO THE BEST OF OUR KNOWLEDGE,
THERE'S NO RECORD

200
00:09:47,029 --> 00:09:49,929
OF WHEN THE PLAY WAS WRITTEN
OR BY WHOM.

201
00:09:52,262 --> 00:09:53,129
-[ GASPS ]

202
00:09:55,295 --> 00:09:57,562
-I HAPPENED TO COME ACROSS
THE SCRIPT

203
00:09:57,562 --> 00:09:59,629
WHILE I WAS CLEANING THE ROOM.

204
00:09:59,629 --> 00:10:03,862
IT WAS SITTING INSIDE
THIS BEAT-UP, OLD BAG.

205
00:10:03,862 --> 00:10:07,162
AFTER THAT WAS WHEN THE STRANGE
RUMORS STARTED FLOATING AROUND.

206
00:10:07,162 --> 00:10:08,462
-ABOUT THE GHOST KNIGHT.

207
00:10:08,462 --> 00:10:10,029
-OF COURSE, IT WAS IMPOSSIBLE

208
00:10:10,029 --> 00:10:12,029
FOR A STORY TO COME TRUE
LIKE THAT.

209
00:10:12,029 --> 00:10:14,895
-BUT IT CERTAINLY MAKES
GOOD ADVERTISING FOR OUR PLAY,

210
00:10:14,895 --> 00:10:16,362
DOESN'T IT?
-SO, ALL --

211
00:10:16,362 --> 00:10:17,562
ALL I HAVE TO DO

212
00:10:17,562 --> 00:10:19,762
IS DANCE THE ROLE
OF THAT GHOST KNIGHT, CORRECT?

213
00:10:19,762 --> 00:10:22,662
-SO YOU'RE REALLY GOING TO
HELP US, THEN, SENIOR FAKIR?

214
00:10:22,662 --> 00:10:24,629
-ALL RIGHT, FAKIR!
BREAK A LEG!

215
00:10:26,662 --> 00:10:29,362
UH, HEY, FAKIR?

216
00:10:31,729 --> 00:10:32,995
-WHAT IS IT?

217
00:10:32,995 --> 00:10:36,795
WHAT IS IT ABOUT THIS STORY
THAT BOTHERS ME SO MUCH?

218
00:10:36,795 --> 00:10:40,995
AND THAT DREAM I HAD --
WHAT THE HELL WAS IT SUPPOSED...

219
00:10:40,995 --> 00:10:43,629
-FAKIR WAS ACTING STRANGE.

220
00:10:43,629 --> 00:10:46,095
I WONDER WHAT WAS WRONG.

221
00:10:46,095 --> 00:10:47,529
WELL, WHATEVER.

222
00:10:47,529 --> 00:10:49,729
HE DECIDED TO DO THE PLAY,

223
00:10:49,729 --> 00:10:53,162
SO I SHOULD BE HAPPY
ABOUT THAT, RIGHT?

224
00:10:53,162 --> 00:10:54,562
BUT, YOU KNOW, I WONDER

225
00:10:54,562 --> 00:10:57,262
IF THERE'S ANYTHING ELSE
I CAN DO FOR MYTHO...

226
00:10:57,262 --> 00:10:59,495
OR IS SEARCHING
FOR HIS HEART SHARDS

227
00:10:59,495 --> 00:11:01,729
REALLY THE ONLY THING
THAT I CAN DO?

228
00:11:01,729 --> 00:11:04,029
-THAT'S RIGHT.
THAT'S RIGHT.

229
00:11:04,029 --> 00:11:07,262
YOU MUSTN'T FORGET THAT,
DEAR, LITTLE DUCK,

230
00:11:07,262 --> 00:11:09,229
DEAR, PATHETIC TUTU,

231
00:11:09,229 --> 00:11:12,995
LEST YOU BE ABANDONED
BY THE STORY,

232
00:11:12,995 --> 00:11:15,295
LEST YOU BE FORGOTTEN.

233
00:11:15,295 --> 00:11:17,162
[ LAUGHS EVILLY ]

234
00:11:17,162 --> 00:11:20,795
[ TCHAIKOVSKY'S "MARCH"
FROM "THE NUTCRACKER" PLAYS ]

235
00:11:34,248 --> 00:11:37,748
-[ GROWLS ]

236
00:11:37,748 --> 00:11:39,981
-WOULD YOU CARE
FOR SOME WATER, FATHER?

237
00:11:39,981 --> 00:11:41,981
-[ ROARS ]

238
00:11:41,981 --> 00:11:43,948
-[ GASPS ]

239
00:11:43,948 --> 00:11:46,048
[ GRUNTS ]

240
00:11:48,081 --> 00:11:49,881
-WHERE IS THE HEART?!

241
00:11:49,881 --> 00:11:53,081
HURRY UP AND BRING ME
A HEART TO EAT!

242
00:11:53,081 --> 00:11:54,515
-I'M SO SORRY, FATHER.

243
00:11:54,515 --> 00:11:57,015
I TRIED HARD
TO CAPTURE YOU A SACRIFICE

244
00:11:57,015 --> 00:11:58,448
IN THE PRINCE'S PLACE.

245
00:11:58,448 --> 00:11:59,581
-YOU DID?

246
00:11:59,581 --> 00:12:01,548
-YES, BUT, FATHER...

247
00:12:01,548 --> 00:12:03,081
-WHAT A WASTE.

248
00:12:03,081 --> 00:12:05,115
YOU WILL NOT BE LOVED BY ANYONE

249
00:12:05,115 --> 00:12:07,548
BUT ME
AND THE PRINCE IN THE STORY.

250
00:12:07,548 --> 00:12:09,581
DO YOU UNDERSTAND ME, DAUGHTER?

251
00:12:09,581 --> 00:12:10,815
AND THERE IS NO WAY

252
00:12:10,815 --> 00:12:13,081
THAT YOU WILL EVER BE LOVED
SO MUCH

253
00:12:13,081 --> 00:12:16,015
THAT SOMEONE WOULD FORFEIT
HIS OWN LIFE FOR YOU.

254
00:12:16,015 --> 00:12:17,748
REMEMBER THAT WELL.
-YES.

255
00:12:17,748 --> 00:12:20,381
-IF YOU STAND
IN THE PRINCE'S WAY AGAIN...

256
00:12:20,381 --> 00:12:23,015
-[ GASPS ]
-...YOU WILL LOSE EVEN MY LOVE.

257
00:12:23,015 --> 00:12:25,681
-I'M SORRY.
I'LL DO THINGS RIGHT NEXT TIME.

258
00:12:25,681 --> 00:12:28,781
-[ GROWLS ]

259
00:12:33,981 --> 00:12:37,448
-THE GHOST KNIGHT IN THE DREAM
AND NOW THIS BOOK?

260
00:12:37,448 --> 00:12:38,915
JUST WHAT DO THEY --

261
00:12:38,915 --> 00:12:40,348
-OH, THERE YOU ARE.

262
00:12:40,348 --> 00:12:42,848
EVERYBODY'S ASSEMBLED ALREADY.

263
00:12:42,848 --> 00:12:44,248
-YES, I'LL BE RIGHT THERE.

264
00:12:46,415 --> 00:12:49,615
WHY WOULD I DREAM ABOUT
THE GHOST KNIGHT?

265
00:12:49,615 --> 00:12:50,648
WHY?!

266
00:12:52,548 --> 00:12:53,715
-[ GASPS ]

267
00:12:53,715 --> 00:12:57,581
-DID THE GHOST KNIGHT SEND ME
THAT DREAM?

268
00:12:58,815 --> 00:13:00,381
THE KNIGHT WHO'S LOST SIGHT

269
00:13:00,381 --> 00:13:02,915
OF THE PLACE
WHERE HE CAN REST HIS SOUL --

270
00:13:02,915 --> 00:13:04,781
IS HE SEEKING SOMETHING FROM ME?

271
00:13:06,315 --> 00:13:09,715
DOES HE WANT ME TO GIVE HIM
A PLACE TO PUT HIS SOUL TO REST?

272
00:13:09,715 --> 00:13:10,881
NO.

273
00:13:10,881 --> 00:13:15,015
MAYBE HE'S PREPARING A PLACE
FOR ME TO DIE.

274
00:13:15,015 --> 00:13:16,615
-IT'S ALMOST KIND OF SCARY.

275
00:13:16,615 --> 00:13:19,181
-IT'S AS IF HE WERE
THE REAL GHOST KNIGHT.

276
00:13:19,181 --> 00:13:21,548
-I'M GOING OUT SHOPPING.
BE BACK SOON.

277
00:13:21,548 --> 00:13:23,848
-SAY, I THINK
I'D PROBABLY BE FASTER.

278
00:13:23,848 --> 00:13:25,215
WANT ME TO GO INSTEAD?

279
00:13:25,215 --> 00:13:27,381
-WOULD YOU?
THEN PLEASE BUY THESE.

280
00:13:27,381 --> 00:13:28,981
-GOT IT.

281
00:13:28,981 --> 00:13:31,548
OKAY.
I DIDN'T FORGET ANYTHING, DID I?

282
00:13:31,548 --> 00:13:35,048
BUT THE TOWN KIND OF FEELS
A LITTLE QUIETER THAN USUAL,

283
00:13:35,048 --> 00:13:38,015
PROBABLY 'CAUSE OF
ALL THE GHOST KNIGHT RUMORS NOW.

284
00:13:38,015 --> 00:13:39,215
[ THUNDER RUMBLES ]

285
00:13:39,215 --> 00:13:40,481
I BETTER HURRY BACK.

286
00:13:51,915 --> 00:13:54,081
[ APPLAUSE ]
-WOW! THAT WAS MARVELOUS!

287
00:13:54,081 --> 00:13:55,481
I HAVE COMPLETE CONFIDENCE

288
00:13:55,481 --> 00:13:57,415
THAT THIS PLAY
WILL BE A SUCCESS!

289
00:13:57,415 --> 00:13:59,015
-WOW!
IT WAS SO BEAUTIFUL!

290
00:13:59,015 --> 00:14:00,348
-WHERE'S DUCK?

291
00:14:00,348 --> 00:14:02,848
-I HAD HER GO
DO SOME SHOPPING FOR ME.

292
00:14:02,848 --> 00:14:05,281
-I SEE.

293
00:14:05,281 --> 00:14:06,448
[ THUNDER CRASHES ]
[ GASPS ]

294
00:14:06,448 --> 00:14:07,615
-SO, WHAT DO YOU SAY?

295
00:14:07,615 --> 00:14:09,948
WOULD YOU DO US THE HONOR
OF FORMALLY BECOMING

296
00:14:09,948 --> 00:14:11,848
A MEMBER OF OUR CLUB,
SENIOR FAKIR?

297
00:14:11,848 --> 00:14:14,048
-I JUST REMEMBERED
SOMETHING I HAVE TO DO.

298
00:14:14,048 --> 00:14:15,681
-WAIT.
SENIOR FAKIR!

299
00:14:15,681 --> 00:14:19,281
-LOOKS LIKE YOU CAN'T HOPE
FOR MUCH FROM HIM AFTER ALL.

300
00:14:19,281 --> 00:14:22,015
[ BIRDS SQUAWKING ]

301
00:14:22,015 --> 00:14:24,715
-YOUR HAIR IS QUITE LOVELY.

302
00:14:24,715 --> 00:14:27,748
IT'S JUST LIKE CROW'S FEATHERS.

303
00:14:27,748 --> 00:14:29,081
-WELL, THANK YOU.

304
00:14:29,081 --> 00:14:32,448
SO, TELL ME, HAVE YOU DECIDED ON
THE NEXT SACRIFICE YET?

305
00:14:32,448 --> 00:14:35,781
-ONLY THE ONES WHO POSSESS
YOUNG AND BEAUTIFUL HEARTS

306
00:14:35,781 --> 00:14:37,348
ARE WORTHY OF SACRIFICE.

307
00:14:37,348 --> 00:14:39,281
I HAVE TO TAKE MY TIME,
YOU KNOW.

308
00:14:39,281 --> 00:14:40,115
-OH.

309
00:14:40,115 --> 00:14:41,448
-GETTING IMPATIENT?

310
00:14:41,448 --> 00:14:42,715
-[ SCOFFS ]

311
00:14:42,715 --> 00:14:45,315
THERE HAVE BEEN
SOME INTERESTING RUMORS LATELY.

312
00:14:45,315 --> 00:14:47,081
-YES.
THE GHOST KNIGHT.

313
00:14:47,081 --> 00:14:49,048
-NOTHING ESCAPES YOU, DOES IT,

314
00:14:49,048 --> 00:14:51,415
NOW THAT YOUR HEART'S
COMING BACK?

315
00:14:51,415 --> 00:14:52,415
-[ CHUCKLES ]

316
00:14:52,415 --> 00:14:54,315
-PRINCES NEED STRONG KNIGHTS.

317
00:14:54,315 --> 00:14:57,748
WHAT IF YOU GOT THE FAMOUS
GHOST KNIGHT ON YOUR SIDE?

318
00:14:57,748 --> 00:14:59,081
-GOOD IDEA.

319
00:14:59,081 --> 00:15:02,048
AFTER ALL, YOU HAVEN'T BEEN ABLE
TO DO ANYTHING, KRAEHE.

320
00:15:02,048 --> 00:15:03,115
-[ SCOFFS ]

321
00:15:03,115 --> 00:15:06,848
-DON'T GET ANGRY.
IT'S THE TRUTH, ISN'T IT?

322
00:15:06,848 --> 00:15:11,848
IN ANY CASE,
I'LL TAKE YOUR ADVICE, KRAEHE.

323
00:15:11,848 --> 00:15:15,015
-WHY AM I GETTING
THIS ILL FEELING?

324
00:15:15,015 --> 00:15:16,681
IS IT THAT SCRIPT?

325
00:15:16,681 --> 00:15:20,081
OR DO I HAVE THE GHOST KNIGHT
TO THANK FOR THIS?

326
00:15:22,648 --> 00:15:23,748
[ BIRD SQUAWKS ]

327
00:15:23,748 --> 00:15:26,015
-[ WHIMPERS ]
THIS IS KIND OF CREEPY.

328
00:15:26,015 --> 00:15:29,715
HEY, WHERE DID THIS TOWN
HAVE A FOREST LIKE THIS?

329
00:15:29,715 --> 00:15:30,848
[ GALLOPING ]

330
00:15:30,848 --> 00:15:31,881
[ GASPS ]

331
00:15:31,881 --> 00:15:33,748
IT'S JUST A HORSE, DUCK.
JUST A HORSE.

332
00:15:33,748 --> 00:15:36,081
THERE'S NO SUCH THING
AS THE GHOST KNIGHT, RIGHT?

333
00:15:36,081 --> 00:15:37,081
NO SUCH THING.

334
00:15:37,081 --> 00:15:39,115
[ HORSE NEIGHS ]
[ GASPS ]

335
00:15:39,115 --> 00:15:41,615
[ GALLOPING ]

336
00:15:41,615 --> 00:15:44,115
IT'S COMING THIS WAY?
NO!

337
00:15:48,281 --> 00:15:50,848
[ GASPS ]

338
00:15:50,848 --> 00:15:53,381
QUACK!

339
00:15:58,381 --> 00:15:59,848
[ WHIMPERING ]

340
00:16:04,581 --> 00:16:06,048
<i>IS THAT HIM?</i>

341
00:16:09,481 --> 00:16:10,948
[ PANTING ]

342
00:16:10,948 --> 00:16:12,015
[ BIRD SQUAWKS ]

343
00:16:12,015 --> 00:16:13,381
HE REALLY IS FOR REAL.

344
00:16:13,381 --> 00:16:14,381
HANG ON.

345
00:16:14,381 --> 00:16:15,481
[ GASPS ]

346
00:16:15,481 --> 00:16:17,281
THEN THE GHOST HAD --

347
00:16:17,281 --> 00:16:18,515
[ GALLOPING ]

348
00:16:18,515 --> 00:16:19,915
HUH? NOT AGAIN!

349
00:16:19,915 --> 00:16:21,148
-DUCK, IS THAT YOU THERE?!

350
00:16:21,148 --> 00:16:22,648
-OH, FAKIR!

351
00:16:22,648 --> 00:16:23,948
[ HORSE NEIGHS ]

352
00:16:23,948 --> 00:16:25,448
JUST NOW, THE GHOST KNIGHT --

353
00:16:25,448 --> 00:16:26,748
-SO YOU SAW HIM?

354
00:16:26,748 --> 00:16:29,015
-YEAH, AND I THINK --
I THINK HE MIGHT BE CARRYING

355
00:16:29,015 --> 00:16:30,948
A SHARD OF MYTHO'S HEART
WITH HIM.

356
00:16:30,948 --> 00:16:31,781
-WHAT?

357
00:16:31,781 --> 00:16:33,048
I SEE.

358
00:16:33,048 --> 00:16:36,481
SO HE STILL HAD A DUTY HE NEEDED
TO DISPATCH AS A KNIGHT.

359
00:16:36,481 --> 00:16:37,748
-WAIT, FAKIR.

360
00:16:37,748 --> 00:16:39,781
YOU'RE NOT GONNA FIGHT
WITH THAT KNIGHT, ARE YOU?

361
00:16:39,781 --> 00:16:41,181
-I AM.

362
00:16:41,181 --> 00:16:43,481
HE'S BEEN SEEKING THE ENEMY
HE'S SUPPOSED TO FIGHT WITH.

363
00:16:43,481 --> 00:16:45,448
-BUT YOU --
-AFTER I DEFEAT HIM,

364
00:16:45,448 --> 00:16:48,281
YOU JUST NEED TO RETURN
THE HEART SHARD TO MYTHO.

365
00:16:48,281 --> 00:16:50,581
-IF WE END UP DYING
ON EACH OTHER'S SWORDS,

366
00:16:50,581 --> 00:16:51,948
JUST LEAVE ME WHERE I LIE.

367
00:16:51,948 --> 00:16:52,948
[ HORSE NEIGHS ]

368
00:16:52,948 --> 00:16:54,052
-FAKIR, HANG ON!

369
00:16:57,865 --> 00:16:59,865
[ HORSE NEIGHS ]

370
00:16:59,865 --> 00:17:00,770
-[ CHUCKLES ]

371
00:17:00,770 --> 00:17:03,837
IT WOULD APPEAR
THAT HORSE ALREADY SENSES

372
00:17:03,837 --> 00:17:05,670
WHO ITS MASTER SHOULD BE.

373
00:17:05,670 --> 00:17:07,337
THAT'S RIGHT.

374
00:17:07,337 --> 00:17:10,204
I CAN GIVE YOU WHAT YOU CRAVE --

375
00:17:10,204 --> 00:17:12,437
AN ENEMY TO DEFEAT.

376
00:17:12,437 --> 00:17:14,170
[ HORSE NEIGHS ]

377
00:17:14,170 --> 00:17:17,004
YOUR SWORD IS SEEKING BLOOD,
ISN'T IT?

378
00:17:17,004 --> 00:17:20,070
CUT DOWN THAT USELESS EXCUSE
FOR A KNIGHT.

379
00:17:20,070 --> 00:17:22,037
-MYTHO.

380
00:17:23,570 --> 00:17:25,804
JUST LIKE THE DREAM.

381
00:17:25,804 --> 00:17:28,537
-NOW, IF YOU ARE A TRUE KNIGHT,
DO THE JOB.

382
00:17:28,537 --> 00:17:31,337
-THEN YOU'RE THE ONE
WHO SHOWED ME

383
00:17:31,337 --> 00:17:33,104
THE END OF THE STORY,
AREN'T YOU?

384
00:17:33,104 --> 00:17:34,704
[ GRUNTS ]

385
00:17:34,704 --> 00:17:35,737
[ SWORDS CLANGING ]

386
00:17:35,737 --> 00:17:38,237
JUST AS YOU WISH,
I'LL TAKE THIS SWORD

387
00:17:38,237 --> 00:17:40,737
AND PLUNGE IT
THROUGH YOUR HEART.

388
00:17:40,737 --> 00:17:44,470
THAT WAY, YOU CAN BE AT PEACE.

389
00:17:44,470 --> 00:17:46,370
-[ PANTING ]
[ GASPS ]

390
00:17:48,370 --> 00:17:49,270
-[ GRUNTS ]

391
00:17:51,304 --> 00:17:52,604
-OH, NO!

392
00:18:09,504 --> 00:18:10,404
-AAH!

393
00:18:10,404 --> 00:18:12,137
[ HORSE NEIGHS ]

394
00:18:12,137 --> 00:18:14,570
[ GRUNTING ]

395
00:18:18,137 --> 00:18:19,370
AAH!

396
00:18:19,370 --> 00:18:20,837
-STOP!

397
00:18:21,870 --> 00:18:23,370
[ GASPS ]

398
00:18:23,370 --> 00:18:25,504
-WHAT THE HELL ARE YOU DOING?!

399
00:18:25,504 --> 00:18:27,070
-[ GASPS ]

400
00:18:27,070 --> 00:18:30,504
PLEASE, FAKIR, DO NOT FIGHT.

401
00:18:30,504 --> 00:18:32,137
-WAIT, TUTU.

402
00:18:32,137 --> 00:18:34,437
DAMN IT, TUTU, WHERE ARE YOU?!

403
00:18:34,437 --> 00:18:35,604
-TUTU.

404
00:18:35,604 --> 00:18:39,070
-PLEASE, COME AND DANCE WITH ME.

405
00:18:47,070 --> 00:18:49,370
AAH!

406
00:18:49,370 --> 00:18:50,804
-TUTU!
WHAT HAPPENED?!

407
00:18:50,804 --> 00:18:52,437
WHERE ARE YOU?!
-STAY AWAY!

408
00:18:52,437 --> 00:18:54,537
[ PANTING ]

409
00:18:58,837 --> 00:19:01,970
NO MATTER HOW MANY TIMES
YOU SWING YOUR SWORD,

410
00:19:01,970 --> 00:19:03,937
YOUR HEART WON'T BE SATISFIED.

411
00:19:03,937 --> 00:19:06,770
I THINK YOU'VE COME
TO THAT REALIZATION.

412
00:19:06,770 --> 00:19:10,270
BECAUSE IT'S NOT YOUR REAL HEART
THAT'S INSIDE YOU NOW.

413
00:19:10,270 --> 00:19:14,837
WHAT DO YOU WANT SO BADLY
THAT YOU TOOK YOUR LOVER'S LIFE?

414
00:19:14,837 --> 00:19:18,737
YOU CAN'T STOP FIGHTING,
EVEN AFTER YOU'VE DIED.

415
00:19:18,737 --> 00:19:20,037
YOU'RE SO SAD.

416
00:19:20,037 --> 00:19:21,670
YOU SUFFER SO MUCH.

417
00:19:21,670 --> 00:19:23,504
YOU HOLD SO MUCH HATE.

418
00:19:23,504 --> 00:19:25,704
WHAT DO YOU WANT THAT MUCH?

419
00:19:25,704 --> 00:19:28,537
IS THIS THING
TRULY SO MUCH MORE PRECIOUS

420
00:19:28,537 --> 00:19:30,004
THAN A LOVER'S LIFE?

421
00:19:31,704 --> 00:19:36,437
PLEASE STOP THIS FIGHTING
AND GIVE BACK MYTHO'S HEART.

422
00:19:36,437 --> 00:19:39,670
-STOP THIS
AND GIVE UP YOUR SWORD.

423
00:19:39,670 --> 00:19:42,537
IT'S TRUE
THAT I'M FROM AN ENEMY KINGDOM,

424
00:19:42,537 --> 00:19:45,570
BUT I'M NOT SAYING IT
FOR MY KINGDOM'S SAKE.

425
00:19:45,570 --> 00:19:47,970
I'M SAYING IT
BECAUSE I LOVE YOU,

426
00:19:47,970 --> 00:19:51,237
BECAUSE I DON'T WANT YOU
TO BEAR ANY MORE SORROW.

427
00:19:56,204 --> 00:19:58,404
[ SWORD CLATTERS ]

428
00:20:00,437 --> 00:20:01,537
-THAT'S RIGHT.

429
00:20:01,537 --> 00:20:04,437
YOUR BATTLE HAS BEEN OVER
FOR A LONG TIME.

430
00:20:07,537 --> 00:20:09,670
-I AM THE FEELING OF PRIDE.

431
00:20:09,670 --> 00:20:11,937
-SO, THE FEELING OF PRIDE.

432
00:20:14,670 --> 00:20:17,604
<i>THE SHARDS OF MYTHO'S HEART</i>
<i>THAT I GIVE BACK</i>

433
00:20:17,604 --> 00:20:19,704
<i>ARE MAKING HIM SUFFER,</i>

434
00:20:19,704 --> 00:20:21,904
<i>BUT THIS IS THE ONLY THING</i>

435
00:20:21,904 --> 00:20:25,170
<i>THAT I CAN DO FOR HIM</i>
<i>RIGHT NOW.</i>

436
00:20:25,170 --> 00:20:27,470
-RIGHT NOW,
I'M THINKING MORE ABOUT

437
00:20:27,470 --> 00:20:30,070
HOW I HAVE TO GET
ALL OF MY FEELINGS BACK

438
00:20:30,070 --> 00:20:31,237
AS SOON AS I CAN,

439
00:20:31,237 --> 00:20:34,437
WITH HELP FROM PRINCESS TUTU,

440
00:20:34,437 --> 00:20:37,437
AND WHEN THAT'S FINISHED,
I'LL GO BACK INTO THE STORY.

441
00:20:37,437 --> 00:20:40,137
-YES, THE PIECES
OF MYTHO'S HEART

442
00:20:40,137 --> 00:20:43,670
SHOULD GO BACK INSIDE MYTHO,
WHERE THEY BELONG.

443
00:20:43,670 --> 00:20:46,670
RIGHT, MYTHO?

444
00:20:46,670 --> 00:20:49,704
-[ GASPING ]

445
00:20:49,704 --> 00:20:51,537
TUTU.

446
00:20:53,670 --> 00:20:57,904
-THE GHOST KNIGHT --
WAS HE ABLE TO DIE?

447
00:20:57,904 --> 00:20:59,137
[ GASPS ]

448
00:21:02,170 --> 00:21:03,804
IT'S DUCK!

449
00:21:19,637 --> 00:21:21,137
-[ WHIMPERS ]

450
00:21:21,137 --> 00:21:25,270
FAKIR, IS IT OKAY
IF I SLEEP A BIT?

451
00:21:27,404 --> 00:21:29,304
-WHY AM I SO WEAK?

452
00:21:29,304 --> 00:21:32,870
CAN MY SWORD
NOT EVEN PROTECT HER?

453
00:21:47,470 --> 00:21:50,137
-[ GASPS ]
NOW I'M IN A BIND.

454
00:21:50,137 --> 00:21:53,904
THERE'S SOMETHING SINISTER
GOING ON THAT I'M NOT A PART OF,

455
00:21:53,904 --> 00:21:56,604
AND EVERY SINGLE ONE
OF MY LITTLE PLAYERS

456
00:21:56,604 --> 00:21:58,370
IS UTTERLY USELESS!

457
00:21:58,370 --> 00:22:02,504
ALAS, IF ONLY EDEL
WERE STILL HERE.

458
00:22:02,504 --> 00:22:04,670
OH, WHAT A BIND.

459
00:22:04,670 --> 00:22:07,670
[ RITSUKO OKAZAKI'S "THOUGH
MY LOVE IS SMALL" PLAYS ]

460
00:22:17,670 --> 00:22:20,670
-[ SINGING IN JAPANESE ]

461
00:23:34,604 --> 00:23:36,037
-I WISH YOU WEREN'T
ALWAYS GOING AROUND

462
00:23:36,037 --> 00:23:37,104
SWINGING SWORDS AND STUFF.

463
00:23:37,104 --> 00:23:39,004
I MEAN,
IT'S REALLY DANGEROUS, YOU KNOW?

464
00:23:39,004 --> 00:23:40,737
-SO YOU THINK I'M INCAPABLE
AS A KNIGHT?

465
00:23:40,737 --> 00:23:41,937
-YOU HAVE RAVEN'S BLOOD

466
00:23:41,937 --> 00:23:44,437
RUNNING THROUGH YOUR VEINS,
JUST LIKE I DO.

